# ccmux-spinner settings.env (example)
#
# Copy to one of these locations and uncomment lines you want to set:
#   - $CCMUX_SPINNER_DIR/settings.env  (default ~/.ccmux-spinner/settings.env)
#   - ./settings.env                   (cwd, project-local; takes priority)
#
# Shell-exported env vars always win over file values.
# Lines starting with # are comments.

# State directory. Reserved for future log files; v0.1 only loads
# this settings.env from it.
# CCMUX_SPINNER_DIR=~/.ccmux-spinner

# tmux pane poll cadence (seconds). The watcher captures pane text
# every interval and yields when the parsed Activity changes.
# CCMUX_SPINNER_POLL_INTERVAL=0.5

# Visual cell width used by `ccmux-spinner watch` for BOTH the
# emit-time separator line and the body trim cap. One knob — the
# block reads as a unit so the two stay synced.
# CCMUX_SPINNER_PRETTY_WIDTH=100
